Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.10,0:00:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A magazine page I can't finish reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.97,0:00:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to read it, but somehow I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.80,0:00:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Game software is stacked in the corner of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.74,0:00:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I don't play them, will they become meaningless?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.65,0:00:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm just beyond the table, and I'm trying to talk with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.64,0:00:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A never changing facial expression is on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.89,0:00:50.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though I'm right here with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.73,0:00:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They can't reach, they can't reach, these feelings of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.91,0:01:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder what's really important?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.47,0:01:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.16,0:01:10.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.63,0:01:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You finally found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.85,0:01:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.87,0:01:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Rebeca Hopkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.72,0:01:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Arthur Hopkin's granddaughter, the man you stole his precious Blue-Eyes White Dragon from!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.32,0:01:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the granddaughter of my grandpa's best friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.12,0:01:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.55,0:01:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now! I'm going to avenge my grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.66,0:01:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Deadly Shadow Ghoul"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.27,0:01:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa didn't steal anyone's card!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.23,0:01:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! He did!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.61,0:02:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know how much my grandpa cherished that card...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.57,0:02:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.56,0:02:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do ya want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.81,0:02:11.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I say something about an important friend of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.06,0:02:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as well as your grandfather, Arthur Hopkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.88,0:02:20.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll just be more of your excuses!\N I don't wanna hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.38,0:02:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.42,0:02:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you want to protect Arthur,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you must hear me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.39,0:02:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine! Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.95,0:02:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened several years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.32,0:02:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.89,0:02:41.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was interested in Duel Monsters, which wasn't very well-known back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.21,0:02:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you could find many rare cards in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.29,0:02:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I left Albal.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.21,0:02:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's where I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.23,0:03:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you'd like, you can have some of my water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.67,0:03:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's so kind of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.79,0:03:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arthur was there to excavate.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.69,0:03:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a good man with a youthful smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.52,0:03:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the archaeological world saw him as a heretic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.95,0:03:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.08,0:03:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.15,0:03:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was also interested in Duel Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.27,0:03:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Rebeca?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.16,0:03:33.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.62,0:03:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In his research of ancient writings,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.67,0:03:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he discovered that a particular word was used over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.99,0:03:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that word is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Game".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Game?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Game?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.03,0:03:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.32,0:03:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that keyword in mind, he retranslated the Egyptian Hieroglyphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.19,0:04:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, he made a startling conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.70,0:04:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.23,0:04:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}According to the ancient text,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the people exchanged scrolls in order to predict the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.03,0:04:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Predict the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To make prophecies of the government and people,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.56,0:04:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they often held rituals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And that was what it meant by exchanging scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.66,0:04:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.57,0:04:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I guess you could call it a sort of ritual card game of some sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.68,0:04:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's Duel Monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This was its inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The card game is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ancient Egyptians played games like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.57,0:04:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This will overturn Ancient Egyptian history.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:05:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, the scientific world...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.08,0:05:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...thought of Arthur's theory as far fetched.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.48,0:05:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite all that, he never gave up his research to find the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.55,0:05:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agreed with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.82,0:05:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, we became good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.79,0:05:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, he believed in the existence of God Cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God Cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.86,0:05:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}One who is able to collect the gods located around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.73,0:05:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}may replace the Sun God Ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.90,0:05:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...as the ruler of this world, like a king.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.28,0:05:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}King of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.01,0:05:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}According to the prophecy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.54,0:05:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the moment all the cards are collected...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.24,0:05:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...will have the power needed to control the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.58,0:05:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The puzzle of the God Cards is not so easy to decipher. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.29,0:05:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to use the rest of my life to research them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.80,0:05:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The God... Cards...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.79,0:06:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Professor Hopkins gave you the Blue-Eyes White Dragon after that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.95,0:06:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar! Liar! Liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.86,0:06:08.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have stole Grandpa's card then!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.27,0:06:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.78,0:06:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Teddy-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.32,0:06:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, Rebeca, a cave-in occurred not long after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:21.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cave-in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.19,0:06:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you alright, Sugoroku-{\i0}san{\i1}?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.10,0:06:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.79,0:06:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.37,0:06:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.76,0:06:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We seem to be trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.76,0:06:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rescue team didn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.64,0:06:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We ran out of food and there was only enough water for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.03,0:06:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.95,0:06:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sugoroku-{\i0}san{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.32,0:06:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.52,0:06:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why don't we play a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.37,0:07:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We shouldn't give up our hope until the very end,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.66,0:07:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but nothing in life is certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At the very least, playing a game will help us to not think about dying as we await our fates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Professor Hopkins...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.76,0:07:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What do you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.30,0:07:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.49,0:07:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We've only got a little bit of water left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But if we want to save one of our lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.64,0:07:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}only one of us can drink it when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.08,0:07:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I propose that the winner of this Duel gets to drink that water. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.63,0:07:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.21,0:07:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Okay! Let's Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.25,0:07:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first turn of the Duel,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arthur played Witch of the Black Forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.90,0:07:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Witch of the Black Forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.87,0:07:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.24,0:07:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arthur taught you this strategy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.00,0:07:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how did it end?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.45,0:07:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it went like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.94,0:07:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.43,0:08:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no proof to back up any of what you're saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.21,0:08:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of attitude is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.27,0:08:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then! It's my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.69,0:08:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oi! Gramps ain't finished yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.38,0:08:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. Let her continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.96,0:08:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The both of you may continue!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.08,0:08:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.30,0:08:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who interrupted the game in the first place! How arrogant!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.99,0:08:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredible though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.11,0:08:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if it's Arthur playing in that ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! I'll use this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.94,0:08:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catapult Turtle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.36,0:08:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catapult Turtle sacrifices one of the Monster on my field...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.66,0:08:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and the opponent takes half of its Attack Power as damage to their Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.67,0:08:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your point is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.60,0:08:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, the Magic Card Brain Control.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.83,0:08:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything but {\i1}that{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This lets me control an enemy Monster for one turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come here, Millennium Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.27,0:09:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the Catapult Turtle launches the Millennium Shield!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.63,0:09:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn's not over yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.26,0:09:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cannon Soldier is defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not fair! Not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.06,0:09:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}-Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.71,0:09:36.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,-Nice one, Yugi! Get 'er!\N - Great attack combo, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.14,0:09:57.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As expected of Yugi Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.19,0:09:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He surely has the skills to be the Duelist Kingdom winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.47,0:10:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There are six Monsters in the Grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.17,0:10:18.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.10,0:10:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it, Teddy-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}-Bravo! Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's {\i1}with{\i0} this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.80,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! I'm gonna win for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.02,0:10:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card! Judgment Bomber!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.16,0:10:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you just say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.44,0:10:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lets me discard five cards from my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.38,0:10:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in exchange...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.44,0:10:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get to destroy every Monster you have on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.71,0:10:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, I Summon Shadow Ghoul to the field in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.35,0:10:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now my favorite number-one cute little baby, Shadow Ghoul, is up to play!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.07,0:11:01.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For every Monster in the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.53,0:11:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this sweety's Attack Power goes up by 100 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.85,0:11:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For {\i1}each{\i0} one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.68,0:11:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has how many Monsters in her Graveyard...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.75,0:11:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,E-Eleven?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.41,0:11:15.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's one hundred times ten?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.11,0:11:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh... the ten goes on the bottom...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.03,0:11:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1,100...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.36,0:11:21.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Now Shadow Ghoul has 2700 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.35,0:11:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sent your Monsters to the Graveyard
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.48,0:11:28.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just to increase Shadow Ghoul's Attack Power?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.37,0:11:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn right I did!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you {\i1}just{\i0} realize that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God, you're {\i1}slow{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.89,0:11:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most important thing in a Duel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.97,0:11:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is one's belief in the Heart of the Cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.29,0:11:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's too much to send your Monsters 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the Graveyard just to gain more power?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.16,0:11:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you {\i1}stupid{\i0} or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.62,0:11:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no "heart" in a Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.67,0:11:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Win at all costs! That's how a real Duelist should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just making up lies
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to cover up for stealing the card!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.45,0:12:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa taught me these tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.23,0:12:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters are just meant to be sacrificed and used as weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.73,0:12:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.29,0:12:16.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Grandpa, I know the ending of this Duel now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yugi, do what you have to do to finish this Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.51,0:12:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know, Grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.80,0:12:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you gonna keep a lady waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.93,0:12:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.52,0:12:32.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon a Monster face-down in Defense Mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, did you know that luck is what determines the outcome of a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.37,0:12:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card! Defense Seal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.38,0:12:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shadow Ghoul, attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wrath of Cemetery!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.98,0:13:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye bye, Black Magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.17,0:13:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps, can't you do anything?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.39,0:13:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still remember how you played this Duel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.68,0:13:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.43,0:13:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.80,0:13:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just sit tight and watch for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The outcome of this battle may yet surprise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sealing Swords of Light!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.45,0:13:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will block the opponent's attacks for three turns!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.41,0:13:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.50,0:13:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.81,0:13:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass this turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.44,0:13:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy for you to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.86,0:13:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll use this!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.14,0:13:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive Black Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.65,0:13:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to block my attacks while preparing for a counter, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.20,0:13:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! No use!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.85,0:13:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll win in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.78,0:13:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't really mind telling you what the card I put face-down is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.24,0:13:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Cannon Soldier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.31,0:13:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Trying to lure me out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.23,0:14:02.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But I can't just leave Cannon Soldier alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.21,0:14:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be avoided!\N Attack Cannon Soldier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.24,0:14:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black Magic!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.70,0:14:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shadow Ghoul's Attack increases even further up by 1000 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.63,0:14:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi seems to be waiting for some card.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.08,0:14:25.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some card?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.17,0:14:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.34,0:14:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's waiting for a big turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.12,0:14:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.41,0:14:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's waiting for some card while the Sealing Swords of Light keeps me trapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it'll be over by the time Shadow Ghoul is done attacking you~!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.47,0:14:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pass this turn as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.17,0:14:46.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Sealing Swords of Light will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.60,0:14:55.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now your Sealing Swords of Light blocking my attacks will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.13,0:14:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll pass again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:14:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then next is my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.74,0:15:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.39,0:15:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's a secret~!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.48,0:15:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Has the card you've been waiting for shown up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.35,0:15:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.37,0:15:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Arthur, you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.30,0:15:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.66,0:15:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you quit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.90,0:15:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.23,0:15:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.46,0:15:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:16:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo! I'm the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.40,0:16:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Teddy-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it! I DID it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.24,0:16:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The card he was waiting for didn't show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.59,0:16:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.86,0:16:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You tore it up! The Blue-Eyes my grandfather cherished more than anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.74,0:16:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.93,0:16:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} why you wouldn't give it back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn! I won't forgive this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.00,0:16:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I really would have given it back from the start, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna hear your excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.26,0:16:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Rebeca.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.97,0:16:37.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Arthur! Is that you, Arthur?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.57,0:16:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see, Sugoroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.42,0:16:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wild granddaughter caused you a lot of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.43,0:16:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My most sincere apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.16,0:16:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca, Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0} won the Duel just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.49,0:16:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way that's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.88,0:17:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, that was a nice Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.02,0:17:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a great Duelist, just like Sugoroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.03,0:17:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.48,0:17:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca, take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.78,0:17:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is called Soul Release.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.44,0:17:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0} used this in his last turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.18,0:17:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it would have removed five cards, along with their very souls, from the Graveyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.46,0:17:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Had he used it, Shadow Ghoul's Attack Power would have dropped from 2800 to 2300,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.00,0:17:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then if it battled with the Black Magician, holding 2500 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.39,0:17:41.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did Yugi surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.51,0:17:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.24,0:17:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.89,0:17:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi-{\i1}kun{\i0} is a boy with a kind heart, just like Sugoroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.37,0:17:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted to save your heart from corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.87,0:17:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the cave-in, Sugoroku lost the Duel on purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.29,0:18:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he let me drink the last of the water, saving my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.88,0:18:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was growing very weak back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.70,0:18:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why did you surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.86,0:18:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Winning is not important. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sugoroku...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I found them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.63,0:18:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're on our way down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.28,0:18:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just sit tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.70,0:18:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca, I did send my Monsters to the Graveyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make Shadow Ghoul more powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.37,0:18:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you need to show respect to the Monsters you sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same in both Dueling and in archeology.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.27,0:19:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duelists must have a caring heart, even in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I gave the Blue-Eyes White Dragon to Sugoroku with a thankful heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.35,0:19:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Sugoroku went and torn that very same card that's so important!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.57,0:19:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry Arthur... The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.20,0:19:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, Sugoroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.86,0:19:22.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've kept it for me all these years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.29,0:19:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's torn,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our friendship is still intact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.99,0:19:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Rebeca. The cards have hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.94,0:19:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A good battle is like a good friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.43,0:19:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hearts?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.44,0:19:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't understand that much, you may as well be disqualified as the American Champ.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.24,0:19:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.45,0:19:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine, Rebeca.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.66,0:19:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.65,0:19:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rebeca, take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.37,0:19:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Bonds of Friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:19:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you'll accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.37,0:19:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.33,0:20:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sugoroku, it's been so long since you and I Dueled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.99,0:20:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and I won't surrender this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.48,0:20:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This'll be fun! Go for it, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.81,0:20:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Gramps, your back is alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.53,0:20:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? As you can see, I'm healthy and ready to-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you alright?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.86,0:20:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} is set up by the Big Five's trap,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.23,0:20:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and is trapped in the Adventure Game World?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.30,0:20:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To save Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}, Yugi and Jounouchi 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.01,0:20:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,enter the game with Mokuba-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.67,0:20:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful. If you don't win the game, you'll never return to the Real World!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.15,0:20:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.68,0:20:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Big Five's Trap: Duel Monsters Quest"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.40,0:20:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.87,0:21:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The flask shines bright
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.11,0:21:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}waiting in the Science Lab
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.48,0:21:18.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}By rubbing our cold hands together...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.72,0:21:25.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They will become warm
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.45,0:21:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An energy shower
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.03,0:21:35.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It'll shower all over you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.09,0:21:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will support your lonely back
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.31,0:21:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}An energy shower
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.29,0:21:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're not alone
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.95,0:22:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because you're surrounded by a ring of friendship
